OVERVIEW — Empire 5
  A multiplayer strategy game of economics and military conquest.

WHAT IS EMPIRE?
  Empire is a turn-based (update-based) multiplayer war game.
  Each player rules a country on a shared hex-grid world map.
  Your goal: grow your economy, build a military, and either
  dominate other nations through conquest or outlast them through
  superior development.

THE WORLD
  The map is a torus (wraps around in both directions).  Sectors
  are hexagonal tiles.  Each sector has a type (gold mine, harbor,
  agribusiness, etc.) that determines what it produces.

  Your country starts with a capital sector at relative position
  (0,0).  All other coordinates are relative to your capital.

THE UPDATE CYCLE
  Everything happens during the update (see info update).
  Between updates you issue commands.  During the update:
    - Sectors produce goods
    - Population grows
    - Distribution moves commodities
    - Ships/units regain mobility
    - Tech, research, education change

THE ECONOMY
  - Civilians work in sectors to produce goods
  - Food keeps civilians alive and growing
  - Gold finances everything (see nation for your treasury)
  - Commodities: iron, LCM, HCM, oil, dust, bars, food, etc.
  - Build sector efficiency over time through good management

THE MILITARY
  - Military defend and attack sectors
  - Ships project power overseas
  - Planes provide air support and bombing
  - Land units lead assaults and occupy territory

GETTING STARTED
  1. census *          see your sectors
  2. resource *        find best sites for mines/farms
  3. des X,Y a         designate agribusiness for food
  4. threshold food * 30    ensure food in all sectors
  5. explore           expand your territory
  6. update            check when next update is

